snippet.textDisplay:
When Nusrat Saab used to sing the opening lines, "Maati Ke Tum Deeware... ", it was just magical. However, not tending towards comparing (as I really think NFAK is beyond compare), this was a wonderful musical treat. It was such a pleasure to watch Amjad saahab's, 'smile of joy' - may your soul rest in peace Sir! We love you and miss you! 

This is obviously a personal opinion - It was a great musical treat but lesser of a divine one. I always imagine, "Rung" as in - Amir Khusro dancing in his courtyard with sublime euphoria and narrating to his mother, "Ma, can you imagine - today I found my teacher/peer (Nizamuddin Aulia),  "Aaj rang hai, ri maa, rang hai ri..., Mohe pir paayo Nizamudin aulia". This Qawwali is a reflection of that joy and ecstasy that Amir Khusro felt at that instance. Its an expression of overflowing happiness in having what you were always looking for. I missed that connection somehow. It was felt in bits when Amjad Saahab sang "Jag Ujiyaaro, jagat ujiyaaro..." but again, that as I said, could be a very personal feeling.

Overall, It was an epic musical treat that I am sure we all will cherish for long time. Special mention to the table player - Out of this world! Thanks Coke Studio for enabling this!

Respect and love from India.
